trans-unit.source: <externalLink><linkText>EnableDeadLetteringOnMessageExpiration</linkText><linkUri>http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/microsoft.servicebus.messaging.queuedescription.enabledeadletteringonmessageexpiration.aspx</linkUri></externalLink>: <parameterReference>True, False</parameterReference>
trans-unit.target: <externalLink><linkText>EnableDeadLetteringOnMessageExpiration</linkText><linkUri>http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/microsoft.servicebus.messaging.queuedescription.enabledeadletteringonmessageexpiration.aspx</linkUri></externalLink>: <parameterReference>True, False</parameterReference>

trans-unit.source: This field controls how the <token>sb2</token> handles a message with an expired TTL.
trans-unit.target: This field controls how the <token>sb2</token> handles a message with an expired TTL.

trans-unit.source: If it is enabled and a message expires, <token>sb2</token> moves the message from the queue into the queue’s dead-letter sub-queue.
trans-unit.target: If it is enabled and a message expires, <token>sb2</token> moves the message from the queue into the queue’s dead-letter sub-queue.

trans-unit.source: If disabled, message is permanently deleted from the queue.
trans-unit.target: If disabled, message is permanently deleted from the queue.

trans-unit.source: Settable only at queue creation time.
trans-unit.target: Settable only at queue creation time.

trans-unit.source: Default: <languageKeyword>false</languageKeyword>
trans-unit.target: Default: <languageKeyword>false</languageKeyword>

trans-unit.source: Enables or disables service-side batching behavior when performing operations for the specific queue.
